<br>
Are you mostly going to be roleplaying, or mostly going to be power gaming? Since this is FV, I'd guess you're gonna be roleplaying... therefore, I'd suggest you go with the RP favorite.<br>
<br>
A shame that your gaming favorite and rp favorite aren't the same. Mine are the same, but I'm wayyy burned out on the warrior class, so my barb warrior combo won't do me well in FV. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucwynlaen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cwynlaen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 2:04:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2840.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Only you can decide</span><hr size=1> The obvious answer, &quot;have two characters,&quot; unfortunately doesn't work on FV for someone with only one account.  Barring that, I'd have to prompt you to redefine your powergaming character's... umm, character... into something easier &amp; more entertaining for you to RP.<br>
<br>
Granted, the paladin class comes with some definite archetypical and stereotypical personality expectations but half the fun might be trying to work what might seem like contrary aspects into your character's make up.  If anything, it would lend a more interesting and credible persona to the character.  Break the mold a little, it could be fun.  <br>
<br>
Paladins don't have to be &quot;Care Bears&quot;.  They could be grudging school of hard knocks teachers too.  They are &quot;holy knights&quot; after all.  They can pull virtues and vices from the opinionated priesthood side as well as the elitest, aristocratic halls of knighthood.  <br>
<br>
Sexuality might seem a little difficult to embed in a paladin's makeup.  Most RPGs I've come across would consider Lancelot as a paladin, and he certainly did have something going on with Gwenivere.  And just a thought, but Norrath doesn't have to be strictured to the Earthly historical analog.  Being a paladin under Erollisi Marr (the Queen of Love) may come with a few expectations and vices of its own.  If anything, you could just resort to being a tease who can't cross that tempting little line no matter how much you like to play on it.  Problems with commitment &amp; conflict with your commitment to the holy order maybe?  Hopelessly devoted to a certain young Gwenivere of your own?  Whatever you can dream up.<br>
<br>
But anyway, which is more consistent of your playing style?  Powergamer or Roleplayer? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaxvs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maxvs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 2:18:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2840.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Only you can decide</span><hr size=1> This one should be easy...<br>
